y plane and I've slanted it so that it's in&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:11.550 --> 00:07:16.020
this horizontal plane, which you should think of&nbsp;
as being essentially horizontal here. And we now&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:16.020 --> 00:07:19.545
have a third dimension or third axis, the
𝑧&nbsp;

00:07:19.545 --> 00:07:26.040
z-axis, running perpendicular from the page.&nbsp;
Our original point, that red one, is now lying&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:26.040 --> 00:07:32.670
in this horizontal plane. Now, I might imagine&nbsp;
a vertical line that goes through this point,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:32.670 --> 00:07:34.020
which is parallel to the
𝑧&nbsp;

00:07:34.020 --> 00:07:39.510
z-axis, so it's actually coming out of&nbsp;
the plane. And now we say, "Oh, we could&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:39.510 --> 00:07:45.900
interpret the point (3, 2) as not representing&nbsp;
that point but actually representing that line."

00:07:45.900 --> 00:07:52.320
So, imagine a three-dimensional creature&nbsp;
that had no two-dimensional visual ability&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:52.320 --> 00:07:57.270
and that could only feel things.&nbsp;
Okay, they could feel things. So,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:57.270 --> 00:08:02.640
a creature like this might have trouble feeling&nbsp;
a dot on a plane but would be very comfortable&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:02.640 --> 00:08:08.910
feeling a line in three-dimensional&nbsp;
space. These are obvious correspondences&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:08.910 --> 00:08:13.680
between points in the plane and lines in&nbsp;
three-dimensional space which are all vertical.

00:08:13.680 --> 00:08:18.990
Here's a third example for the same thing.&nbsp;
We still have a plane now lying horizontally.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:18.990 --> 00:08:24.030
There is our original point. But now what&nbsp;
I'm doing is I'm fixing a point on the&nbsp;

00:08:24.030 --> 00:08:25.830
𝑧
z-axis, some fixed&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:25.830 --> 00:08:33.630
black dot. And what I'm doing is I'm connecting&nbsp;
points on the plane with this fixed black dot to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:33.630 --> 00:08:41.850
make lines which are all going through that&nbsp;
point. Now, I can interpret this point (3,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:41.850 --> 00:08:46.140
2) as not representing this dot, not&nbsp;
representing the vertical line through it,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:46.140 --> 00:08:51.420
but rather representing this slanted&nbsp;
line through the point and our fixed dot.

00:08:51.420 --> 00:08:58.920
In this picture, theorems of geometry become&nbsp;
theorems about these lines through this fixed&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:58.920 --> 00:09:05.130
point. Any theorem in Euclidean geometry that you&nbsp;
can frame, you can reformulate in terms of the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:05.130 --> 00:09:10.290
picture about lines that have this particular&nbsp;
property. And it might be that on some other&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:10.290 --> 00:09:15.660
planet, this is a preferred way of thinking&nbsp;
about things. So, we're not going to say that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:15.660 --> 00:09:21.510
one of these is better than the other. We can use&nbsp;
whichever one is convenient to us. The definition&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:21.510 --> 00:09:27.930
rides above all interpretations of it and&nbsp;
gives us a flexibility that can be very useful.

